Subject: [PATCH 1/7] =?UTF-8?q?Add=20"=D0=9A=D0=BE=D0=BD=D1=82=D1=80=D0=BE?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=D0=BB=D1=8C"=20column=20(green=20=E2=9C=93=20/=20red=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=9C=97)=20to=20the=20two=20daily=20reports?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The temperature limits shown in the reports (Режим °C) come from the management
conditions whose template/owner has the "Участвует в отчёте" (inReport) checkbox.

Adds one column to each report plus the OK/NOT-OK property behind it (BOOLEAN):
- limitReport: reportControl(Device, MeasurementType, ZDATETIME) — TRUE when the
  reading at the report time is within [min..max]; new jrxml column.
- routeReport: routeControl(Location, MeasurementType, DATE) — TRUE when no reading
  during the route window leaves the device limits; fills the existing placeholder.
The cell renders a green check (✓) / red cross (✗) via a conditional jrxml style
(DejaVu Sans font, which carries the glyphs).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
